review_blob: 12 is. bottle. Pours murky golden with thin, white head that quickly dissipates to a ring along the glass. Aroma is a very sweet, yeasty essence that is quite strong. You can smell it immediately upon opening. Initial taste is somewhat weak with an aftertaste of dough and yeast. A sweet and yeasty golden drink that goes well with salty foods. Average beer, below average for New Glarus.
Murky golden color, thin white head when poured. Very slight aroma of wheat and spice. Refreshing and crisp aftertaste. Great summer beer that pairs well with a good fish fry.
